<div>
	<div  class="integration-section-2">
		<div class="scrow" onclick="showContent2()">
			<div>Collect opinions directly on your site</div>
			<div><i class="fas fa-angle-down"></i></div>
		</div>
	<div class="integration-content-2">
		<p>With this feature you can collect opinions from your audience without
			using EJ interface directly. This component can be included in your
			site's html, and it will allow users to participate on conversations
			and add comments from within your personal site.
		</p>
		<p>
			To add this conversation to your site/platform, add the following
			snippet of code to your page header:

			<div class="integration-section-2-snippet">
				<div>
					<code>&lt;script src='https://unpkg.com/ej-conversations@0.0.2/dist/conversations.js'&gt&lt;/script&gt</code>
					<br>
					<code>&lt;link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway&display=swap' rel="stylesheet"&gt&lt;/link&gt</code>
					<br>
					<code>&lt;link href='{{schema}}://{{request.META['HTTP_HOST']}}/static/css/fontawesome-all.min.css' rel="stylesheet"&gt&lt;/link&gt</code>
				</div>
			</div>

			and this snippet of code on the page body:

			<div class="integration-section-2-snippet">
				<div>
					<code>&lt;ej-conversation host={{schema}}://{{request.META['HTTP_HOST']}}
					cid="{{conversation.id}}"&gt&lt;/ej-conversation&gt</code>
				</div>
			</div>
		</p>
	</div>
</div>
   <script>
	   function showContent2() {
		   let content = document.querySelector(".integration-content-2");
		   let section = document.querySelector(".integration-section-2");
		   if (window.getComputedStyle(content).maxHeight == "0px") {
			content.style.maxHeight = "400px";
			section.style.borderRadius = "unset";
			section.style.borderStyle = "unset";
		   }
		   else {
			content.style.maxHeight = "0px";
			section.style.borderStyle = "solid";
			section.style.borderRadius = "1rem";
		   }
	   }
   </script>
